  "text": "As an effect of Manganese alloying, Ferrite transformed into Austenite. Manganese is well known an Austenite phase stabilizer which could make an Austenite phase stable at lower temperature. This phase is desirable in the fabrication of Fe-Mn-C biomaterials because it is not magnetic, so it does not interfere with examination using MRI. Hermawan et al. showed the magnetic susceptibility of Fe-35Mn is about ∼1.8 × 10 −7 m 3 /kg which considered as nonmagnetic materials [CITATION_1] .",
